{% extends "layout.html" %}

{% block title %}Coding — Stella Fusaro{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="video-background">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="{{ url_for('static', filename='homepage.mp4') }}" type="video/mp4">
    Your browser does not support the video tag.
  </video>
</div>

<section class="coding-overlay">
  <h1>Coding Projects</h1>
  <p class="intro">
    Here's a selection of my programming projects, spanning mobile development, web design, creative applications, and experimental user experiences. You can explore more on <a href="https://github.com/stellafusaro" target="_blank">my GitHub</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="project-grid">

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Dance NYC (in progress) <span>Android App — Java / Android Studio</span></h2>
      <p>
        A mobile app designed to help users easily locate dance classes in NYC. I led the design and development using Java in Android Studio, with a focus on streamlined UI and real-time location filtering.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Spotify Genre Playlist Generator <span>Python / Spotify API</span></h2>
      <p>
        A Python-based tool that connects to the Spotify API to generate custom playlists by genre. It pulls track data and builds personalized recommendations based on user input and listening preferences.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/stellafusaro/Spotify-Genres" target="_blank">
    <img src="https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api/pin/?username=stellafusaro&repo=Spotify-Genres&theme=default" alt="Spotify Genre Generator" class="github-card">
  </a>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Poker Simulator <span>Java</span></h2>
      <p>
        A console-based poker game built in Java, complete with logic for gameplay, betting rounds, and randomized card dealing. Focused on simulating strategy and game flow.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/stellafusaro/poker" target="_blank">
    <img src="https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api/pin/?username=stellafusaro&repo=poker&theme=default" alt="Poker Simulator" class="github-card">
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>Ballet Database Website <span>HTML / CSS / Flask</span></h2>
      <p>
        A searchable database of ballets with detailed information and a homepage design. Users can search by title, choreographer, or genre. Built with a clean interface and functional backend.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/stellafusaro/ballet-database-website" target="_blank">
    <img src="https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api/pin/?username=stellafusaro&repo=ballet-database-website&theme=default" alt="Ballet Database" class="github-card">
  </a>
    </div>

    <div class="project">
      <h2>How to Use a Camera Website <span>HTML / CSS / Flask</span></h2>
      <p>
        An interactive learning site explaining the exposure triangle — ISO, aperture, and shutter speed. Includes photo examples, a quiz, and a custom-built camera simulator. The site is narrated by “Stacey,” a fictional influencer hiring users to take her photo, adding a humorous narrative layer.
      </p>
<a href="https://github.com/milatabach/stacy_the_sassy" target="_blank">
    <img src="https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api/pin/?username=milatabach&repo=stacy_the_sassy&theme=default" alt="Stacy the Sassy" class="github-card">
  </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .video-background {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
    z-index: -1;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .video-background video {
    width: 100vw;
    height: 100vh;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
  }

  .coding-overlay {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 6rem 2rem;
    font-family: sans-serif;
    color: black;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .coding-overlay h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem auto;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #444;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .project-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .project h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .project h2 span {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
  }

  .project p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #333;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

.project {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}

</style>
{% endblock %}

